  "title": "Part-Time Tutor (Chinese - Primary Level)",
  "description": "<p>Position: Part-Time Chinese Tutor (Primary Level)</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Location: West Coast Plaza</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Hours: Flexible, based on availability and scheduling needs</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>About Us: We are a dynamic and dedicated tutoring center committed to helping students achieve academic excellence. Our focus is on providing personalized instruction to enhance understanding and foster a love for learning. We are currently seeking an enthusiastic and knowledgeable Chinese tutor to join our team on a full/part-time basis.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Provide one-on-one or small group tutoring sessions in Chinese for students at various levels (Primary 1-6).</li>\n  <li>Develop and implement engaging lesson plans tailored to each student's needs and learning style.</li>\n  <li>Assist students with homework, exam preparation, and understanding key Chinese concepts.</li>\n  <li>Track and report on students' progress and adjust teaching strategies as needed.</li>\n  <li>Maintain a positive, encouraging, and patient attitude towards students.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor's degree or higher in Chinese Language or a related field.</li>\n  <li>Previous tutoring or teaching experience preferred.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of Chinese Language curriculum and exam requirements.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.</li>\n  <li>Patience and passion for teaching and helping students succeed.</li>\n  <li>Ability to commit to a consistent schedule and be punctual.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Competitive hourly rate.($30 - 80/hr)</li>\n  <li>Flexible scheduling.</li>\n  <li>Opportunity to make a significant impact on students' academic success.</li>\n  <li>Supportive and collaborative work environment.</li>\n</ul>",
